[SN]TITLE[SN]
Fundraiser for marina death fisherman Lee Turner

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A fishing competition in memory of a fisherman who died after falling into Swansea marina is being held on Sunday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Lee Turner, 45, disappeared on 7 November after being seen falling into the water.
His body was recovered from the marina ten days later.
The competition is being held at the Swansea Bay seafront near County Hall, with all proceeds being donated to the Royal National Lifeboat Institution.
